cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.CR, cs.AI, cs.NE 

The paper discusses the use of machine learning models, specifically deep architectures, and their susceptibility to adversarial samples. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the sub-categories of machine learning (cs.LG), computer vision (cs.CV), and cryptography and security (cs.CR). The proposed method of using direct density ratio estimation to detect adversarial samples also suggests that the paper may belong to the sub-categories of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE).
